It is invented by Guido van Rossum in 1991
Uses of Python 
-Web development 
-Software development 
-Mathmatics 
-System scriptng
-Data science 

Why Python 
-Python work on different platforms (Window,Mac ,Linux ,Raspberry Pi etc)

Python automatically identifies the types of variables 

Variable & datatypes 
-A variables is the name given to  a memory location in a program 

Datatypes
-Primarily these are following data type in python
a. Integer - It hold the numberical value 
    for eg-1,2,-1
Inbuilt function and operation for Integer :
num=10;
1. print(abs(num))  ##Absolute value
output->10
2. print(bn(num))  ##binary representation 
output->1010
3. print(hex(num))  ##hexa representation 
output->Oxa 
3. print(pow(num,2))  ##power function
output->100
4. print(divmod(num,3))  ##Quouient & Remainder
output->3,1

b. Floating no.-It will take decimal number
   for eg-1.1,24.5 
Inbuilt function and operation for float :
1. print(round(price))  ## Round
  output -> 100

-Typecasting
--print(int(price))->convert to integer
output-=99
--print(Float("1234))->convert string  to integer
output-=1234

 c. String (greeting="hello world!")

Inbuilt function and operation for String :
1. print(greeting.lower())   ##convert to lower
2. print(greeting.upper())   ##convert to upper
3. print(greeting.replace("world","python"))   ## for Replace substring 
4. print(greeting.split())  ##split string into a list 
5. print(greeting.find("world") ## find the world of substring  
6. print(len(greeting))  ##length of string

d.List[]- It is mutable(can be change) .It is container to store a set of value of any data type
eg fruit=["apples","banana","cherry"]

Inbuilt function and operation for list:
1.Append - It always add at end of the list 
2. Extend- It also  add at end of the list
3.Remove- It remove an element 
4.Pop- It remove the last element
5. Sort - It sort the list 
6.len - length of list 
7. index - find the index of particular value 

c.Tuple() - It is immutable (cannot be change )
   Coordinates=(10.0,20.0)
Inbuilt function and operation for tuple :
1.count - how many time a number is occurs 
2. index - find the index of particular 
3. len - length of the tuple
You can change in tuple by converting tuple into list  
for eg : coordiante=(10.0,20.0);
  Now convert in list :
li=list(coordinate)
Now print (li)
[10.0,20.0]

d.Dictinory - Dictinory is a collection of key value
syntax- person {name : "Pranav"}
Inbuilt function and operation for Dictinory :
1.print (person.key())  ##Get all keys
2. print (person.value())  ##Get all value
3. print (person.iteam()) ## Get all key value pair 
4.update - update dictinory with another dictinory
5. pop - for remove the value
6.length - to check the length of the dictinory


e. Set - It is a collection of non repetitive element 
- for eg se={1,2,3,4} 
- not allow  duplicates
-length = to check the length 
- add = to add the value

Conditional statement :
-if 
-elif
-else
for eg:   
a = 200
b = 33
if b > a:
  print("b is greater than a")
elif a == b:
  print("a and b are equal")
else:
  print("a is greater than b")

 In this example conditon third is working conditon 1 and 2  follow the condition  


















